<br>
Everyone is welcome to attend but I do have a few rules...<br>
<br>
One you must be 54 or better to attend my PoG raids.<br>
<br>
Two last piece rule does apply...but last piece must be confirmed by inspection.<br>
<br>
All items are opened lottoed for that class and will be done on a 150 300 random..high wins.<br>
<br>
If you win one item you must wait till everyone in your class wins an item untill you can lotto again.    <br>
<br>
   Even if you win a bracer and a BP drops..you won..you are out on BP lotto.<br>
<br>
   If a cleric comes in half way threw and all the clerics that have been there have won...then you can reenter the lotto even though the new cleric has not won.<br>
<br>
  Spells will be a seperate lotto but same basic rules will apply.  Extra spells go to me...ie no one of that class there or everyone there of that class already has spell.<br>
<br>
  Gems go to me.  They will be distributed amoung clerics, and depending chanters/mages for reagents except for Blue Diamonds which will be kept for resist gear.<br>
<br>
  If you join after we have started the raid ... you must have been at the raid a full 30 min before you get to win an item...unless of course you are the only person of that class present.<br>
<br>
  I would request that no one ask for a certain type of mob to be pulled.  If you do it repeatedly while I am pulling I will ask you to leave.  <br>
<br>
  Twinks who are 54 and attend the raid will be allowed to lotto against mains.   Why?  This is not a guild event...I dont know who main and twinks are...if your 54 your good enough for this raid so your good enough to win.  If the person is a twink and WANTS to default to another person..that is fine too.<br>
<br>
Why 54...well...lots of reasons and I am sure its very controversial ...but ah well.<br>
<br>
I think all these rules are fair.  If anyone has a logical objection to them...thats kewl...tell me or write it here...I might change my mind.  If not...just know going in these are the rules.<br>
<br>
I hate loot disputes.  I have seen it time and time again..thats why I went into such detail here.<br>
<br>
